The paper deals with change detection in high-resolution satellite images using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method also involves the use of dual-attention mechanism and weighted double margin contrastive loss, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of remote sensing images, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
